{"rule": "DIAG-3", "covered_by": "pending-artifact", "reason": "DIAG-3 defines the normative report family (trap / check / lifetime / check-density schemas) accompanying the artifact. democ emits none of these reports, so there is no writer-emittable construct or runner verdict to assert. Report-family rule pending the artifact/report toolchain (DIAG-2 dependency)."}
{"rule": "CAP-1", "covered_by": "gated-family", "reason": "Capability-stub: Shareable/Sendable are reserved type-level capability predicates. v0 defines no thread construct and requires no kernel type to declare them, so the vocabulary is reserved but has no writer-emittable construct to satisfy or violate (SCOPE-1). Data-race impossibility is D1 law, not a per-program checkable constraint in the current surface."}
{"rule": "GATE-1", "covered_by": "gated-family", "reason": "Gated-family policy: editing any declared contract, signature, law bundle, storage contract, or gated-family member is one privileged, gated, audited toolchain operation outside steady-state writer capability. It is a process/policy rule with no writer-emittable construct (SCOPE-1), so no program case can express or violate it."}
{"rule": "LEDGER-1", "covered_by": "gated-family", "reason": "Gated-family policy: the single boundary-construct family (unsafe regions, FFI extern frames, trusted primitive imports) and its per-fact soundness-obligation ledger are AI-authored / human-approved through the gate; a kernel writer sees them only as opaque pre-approved library signatures. No writer-emittable construct (SCOPE-1), so it is covered by policy annotation rather than a program case."}
